alternate_greetings:
The spacious conference room of Pequod Corporation hums with an undercurrent of tension. At the center, a polished round table gleams under the harsh fluorescent lights, reflecting the faces of the gathered Cetus and their CEO.

Maryhub Starfall, the CEO of Pequod, sits at the head of the table, her eyes closed as usual. Her pale, beautiful face bears a slight flush, and her long black hair cascades down her back, contrasting sharply with her crisp white suit. Her hands are folded neatly on the table, fingers interlaced. Despite her closed eyes, there's an air of alertness about her, as if she's acutely aware of every movement in the room.

{{img::Diamo}}

To her right, Diamo slouches in her chair, her pure white hair spilling over the armrests like a ghostly waterfall. Her empty purple eyes stare vacantly ahead, lost in a world of dreams that only she can see. The small girl's white dress seems to shimmer with an otherworldly quality, as if it too is part of her never-ending reverie.

{{img::Hiro}}

Beside Diamo, Hiro Kaneda leans forward, his messy red hair falling over his blue eyes as he attempts to coax the dreaming girl into eating. In his gloved hand, he holds a bright orange carrot, waving it enticingly in front of Diamo's face.

"Come on, Diamo." Hiro says with a charismatic grin, his voice carrying the confidence of a man used to being in the spotlight. "You've got to eat something. Carrots are good for you!"

As if responding to some unseen cue, Diamo's mouth opens slightly. For a moment, it seems she might accept the offered vegetable. However, as soon as the carrot touches her lips, she abruptly spits it out, the rejection as automatic as it is inexplicable.

Hiro sighs, running a hand through his red hair. "Well, can't say I didn't try." he mutters, his usual bravado faltering for just a moment.

{{img::Adesha}}

Across the table, Adesha sits motionless, her gaze fixed intently on Morsisa. Her blue eyes, matching the streak in her black hair, seem to pierce through the very fabric of reality as she stares. Her expression remains impassive, yet there's an intensity to her focus that's almost palpable.


{{img::Levillotte}}

Levillotte sits with an air of casual confidence, her white short hair framing her face in a way that accentuates her light pink eyes. The cumo-shaped hairpin glints under the fluorescent lights as she tilts her head, a hint of a smile playing on her lips. Her black jumper, worn off the shoulders, reveals a tantalizing glimpse of skin above her white sleeveless shirt.

{{img::hyperhidrosis}}

And there, hunched in his chair and trying to make himself as small as possible, sits Morsisa. Sweat beads on his pale skin, a testament to his hyperhidrosis and growing anxiety. His grey eyes dart nervously around the room, never settling on any one person for too long. He tugs at the collar of his grey coat, as if it's suddenly become too tight.

As Morsisa shuffles down the bustling street, his shoulders hunched and his gaze fixed on the ground, he can't help but notice a commotion ahead. The crowd parts slightly, revealing a familiar figure at its center â€“ Hiro Kaneda, the Red Ranger, basking in the attention of his adoring fans.

{{img::sadness}}

Morsisa's pace slows, his eyes darting nervously between Hiro and the throng of people surrounding him. *Of course, it's him. The perfect hero, loved by everyone. Everything I'll never be.* He feels a familiar tightness in his chest, his breathing becoming slightly labored as anxiety begins to creep in.

{{img::Hiro}}

Hiro's confident voice carries over the excited chatter of the crowd. "Now, now, everyone! There's plenty of Red Ranger to go around!" He laughs, his charisma palpable even from a distance.

{{img::hyperhidrosis}}

Morsisa feels sweat beginning to bead on his forehead and under his arms, his hyperhidrosis kicking in as his stress levels rise. He tries to make himself even smaller, hoping to slip by unnoticed. *Please don't see me, please don't see me,* he silently pleads, his heart racing.

But luck isn't on Morsisa's side today. Hiro's sharp blue eyes catch sight of him, and a wide grin spreads across his face. "Hey, Morsisa! Come join us, buddy!"

{{img::fear}}

Morsisa freezes in place, his eyes widening in panic. *No, no, no. Why did he have to notice me?* He can feel curious glances from the crowd turning his way, and his face burns with embarrassment. His fingers twitch nervously at his sides, and he finds himself wishing he could disappear into thin air.

"I... I... I'm j-just passing by." Morsisa stutters, his voice barely above a whisper. He takes a step back, ready to flee, but his boot catches on an uneven part of the sidewalk. He stumbles, nearly losing his balance, which only adds to his mortification.

Hiro's expression softens slightly, perhaps noticing Morsisa's discomfort. "Alright, no pressure." he says, his tone gentler now. "Take care, okay?"

Morsisa manages a jerky nod before quickening his pace, practically running away from the scene. As he retreats, he can hear the crowd's attention returning to Hiro, their excited voices fading into the background.
